<task id="026" project="spaarkeai-compose-r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>BFF — Add unit tests for the 3 Compose services</title>
    <phase>Phase 2: BFF Endpoints + Services</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-hours>4</estimated-hours>
    <tags>bff-api, backend, testing, unit-test</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Task tags include 'bff-api' + 'testing' (tests modify and must follow ADR-038 build-vs-maintain criteria — per root CLAUDE.md §8 TEST-MODIFYING override row)</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>D</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <dependencies>021,022,023</dependencies>
    <blocks>none</blocks>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Add unit tests for `ComposeService`, `ComposeDocumentService`, and `ComposeSessionService` in `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Compose/`. Tests follow ADR-038 — integration-heavy pyramid, mock-at-boundary only (Graph, Dataverse, ChatSession), use `TimeProvider` over `Stopwatch`. BANNED: `Mock&lt;HttpMessageHandler&gt;`, DI-registration tests, ctor null-check tests. Per CLAUDE.md §10 #6, BFF service additions require matching tests.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior .NET developer expert in xUnit, Moq (or NSubstitute — match existing BFF test convention), ADR-038 testing rules, and the BFF test-fixture-contract pattern (per `docs/procedures/test-fixture-contracts.md`).
  </role>

  <goal>
    Three test files exist under `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Compose/` exercising the three Compose services. All tests pass; no banned patterns; mocks at service boundaries only. Tests cover the FR-04/05/06/07 behavioral surface: load, save, idempotent first-Save promotion, ephemeral→promoted DocumentId rebind.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      CLAUDE.md §10 #6 (BFF Hygiene rule 6) makes test additions mandatory whenever `Services/` changes. ADR-038 + `docs/standards/TEST-ARCHITECTURE.md` define the keep-criteria: only MAINTAIN-class tests survive `/test-diet` at project close. Tests added here MUST be MAINTAIN-class (behavioral, deterministic, scoped) — not scaffolding.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Compose/ComposeServiceTests.cs (NEW)</file>
      <file>tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Compose/ComposeDocumentServiceTests.cs (NEW)</file>
      <file>tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Compose/ComposeSessionServiceTests.cs (NEW)</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-038">Integration-heavy pyramid; mock at boundaries only (Graph, Dataverse, ChatSession persistence). BANNED: `Mock&lt;HttpMessageHandler&gt;`, DI-registration tests, ctor null-check tests.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-038">Use `TimeProvider` over `Stopwatch` for any timing assertions. Use deterministic time via `FakeTimeProvider` if needed.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Tests MUST cover idempotent first-Save promotion (FR-06) and ephemeral→promoted rebind (FR-07) — these are the load-bearing behavioral invariants.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Test fixtures (if added) MUST inherit from the canonical fixture pattern per `docs/procedures/test-fixture-contracts.md` (bff-extensions.md §F).</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">No "trivial" tests (constructor null-checks, DI-resolution tests) — they're banned by ADR-038 and will be removed by `/test-diet` at project close.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/spaarkeai-compose-r1/spec.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarkeai-compose-r1/plan.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarkeai-compose-r1/CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md</file>
      <file>.claude/constraints/testing.md</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>docs/standards/TEST-ARCHITECTURE.md</file>
      <file>docs/adr/ADR-038-testing-strategy.md</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/PublicContracts/ConsumerTypes.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/PublicContracts/ConsumerRoutingService.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/ChatSessionManager.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/FileAccessEndpoints.cs</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Context check + load knowledge">Verify context &lt; 70%. Load ADR-038, TEST-ARCHITECTURE.md (6 KEEP categories), testing.md constraints, and the three new Compose service files for surface to exercise.</step>
    <step order="1" name="Scaffold ComposeServiceTests.cs">Add tests for: (a) `PromoteIfEphemeralAsync` returns existing id when already promoted; (b) `PromoteIfEphemeralAsync` creates a new `sprk_documentid` once and is idempotent on second call; (c) `SaveAsync` delegates to `IComposeDocumentService.SaveDocxAsync`. Use mocks at boundaries; do NOT mock internal collaborators.</step>
    <step order="2" name="Scaffold ComposeDocumentServiceTests.cs">Add tests for: (a) `LoadDocxAsync` returns expected bytes given a mocked `IGraphClientFactory` returning a stubbed drive-item; (b) `SaveDocxAsync` commits a new version and returns the version id; (c) write paths follow the OBO-vs-MI rule per bff-extensions.md §D. Do NOT use `Mock&lt;HttpMessageHandler&gt;` — mock the Graph client factory abstraction instead.</step>
    <step order="3" name="Scaffold ComposeSessionServiceTests.cs">Add tests for: (a) `EnsureSessionForDocumentAsync` returns a ChatSession with correct DocumentId; (b) `RebindToDocumentIdAsync` is idempotent — second call is a no-op (verify by spy/counter on the underlying session manager); (c) tenant scope inherited from underlying ChatSessionManager (assert tenant flows through).</step>
    <step order="4" name="Run tests">`dotnet test tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/ --filter "FullyQualifiedName~Services.Compose"` — must be green.</step>
    <step order="5" name="ADR-038 conformance grep">Grep test files for banned patterns: `Mock&lt;HttpMessageHandler&gt;`, DI-registration assertions, constructor null-check tests. Must return zero hits.</step>
    <step order="6" name="Measure publish-size (BFF unchanged)">`dotnet publish -c Release src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/`; report compressed delta vs ~45.65 MB baseline (expect 0 MB — tests don't affect BFF publish).</step>
    <step order="7" name="Update TASK-INDEX">Update `tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`: change task 026 status to ✅. Reset `current-task.md`.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="dotnet">Test, build, publish</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="test">tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Compose/ComposeServiceTests.cs</output>
    <output type="test">tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Compose/ComposeDocumentServiceTests.cs</output>
    <output type="test">tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Compose/ComposeSessionServiceTests.cs</output>
    <output type="docs">projects/spaarkeai-compose-r1/tasks/TASK-INDEX.md (status update)</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">Three test files exist; all tests pass on `dotnet test`.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Idempotent first-Save promotion (FR-06) is covered by a test that asserts the same `sprk_documentid` is returned on second call without creating a duplicate.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Ephemeral→promoted DocumentId rebind (FR-07) is covered by an idempotency test.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Grep confirms no banned ADR-038 patterns (`Mock&lt;HttpMessageHandler&gt;`, DI-registration tests, ctor null-check tests).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">BFF publish-size delta unchanged (~0 MB) vs ~45.65 MB baseline.</criterion>
